{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"## Summary\\n\\n49 cytochrome-P450 monooxygenase activity terms with EC:1.14.14.x xrefs are currently descendants of GO:0016709 *oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, ... NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen* (EC:1.14.13.-). They should be reparented under GO:0016712 (EC:1.14.14.-, *...reduced flavin or flavoprotein as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen*), matching the IUBMB 2018 reclassification of most cytochrome-P450 enzymes from EC sub-subclass 1.14.13 to 1.14.14.\\n\\nThe target grouping term GO:0016712 already exists with `xref: EC:1.14.14.- {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}`.\\n\\n## Affected terms (49)\\n\\n| GO ID | Name | EC |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| GO:0004506 | squalene monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.17 |\\n| GO:0008398 | sterol 14-demethylase activity | 1.14.14.154 |\\n| GO:0010295 | (+)-abscisic acid 8'-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.137 |\\n| GO:0016710 | trans-cinnamate 4-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.91 |\\n| GO:0016711 | flavonoid 3'-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.82 |\\n| GO:0018664 | benzoate 4-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.92 |\\n| GO:0033772 | flavonoid 3',5'-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.81 |\\n| GO:0033775 | deoxysarpagine hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.136 |\\n| GO:0033777 | lithocholate 6beta-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.138 |\\n| GO:0033781 | cholesterol 24-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.25 |\\n| GO:0036189 | abieta-7,13-diene hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.144 |\\n| GO:0036201 | ent-isokaurene C2-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.76 |\\n| GO:0036202 | ent-cassa-12,15-diene 11-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.112 |\\n| GO:0036204 | abieta-7,13-dien-18-ol hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.145 |\\n| GO:0036209 | 9beta-pimara-7,15-diene oxidase activity | 1.14.14.111 |\\n| GO:0047082 | 3,9-dihydroxypterocarpan 6a-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.93 |\\n| GO:0047083 | 5-O-(4-coumaroyl)-D-quinate 3'-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.96 |\\n| GO:0047084 | methyltetrahydroprotoberberine 14-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.97 |\\n| GO:0047087 | protopine 6-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.98 |\\n| GO:0047088 | dihydrosanguinarine 10-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.100 |\\n| GO:0047089 | dihydrochelirubine 12-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.101 |\\n| GO:0047957 | 4'-methoxyisoflavone 2'-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.89 |\\n| GO:0048000 | isoflavone 3'-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.88 |\\n| GO:0050591 | quinine 3-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.55 |\\n| GO:0050592 | 4-hydroxyphenylacetaldehyde oxime monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.37 |\\n| GO:0050593 | N-methylcoclaurine 3'-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.102 |\\n| GO:0050594 | tabersonine 16-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.103 |\\n| GO:0050596 | vinorine hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.104 |\\n| GO:0050597 | taxane 10-beta-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.105 |\\n| GO:0050598 | taxane 13-alpha-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.106 |\\n| GO:0102001 | isoleucine N-monooxygenase (oxime forming) activity | 1.14.14.39 |\\n| GO:0102002 | valine N-monooxygenase (oxime forming) activity | 1.14.14.38 |\\n| GO:0102068 | alpha-humulene 10-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.113 |\\n| GO:0102170 | 5-epi-aristolochene-1,3-dihydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.149 |\\n| GO:0102289 | beta-amyrin 11-oxidase activity | 1.14.14.152 |\\n| GO:0102320 | 1,8-cineole 2-exo-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.56 |\\n| GO:0102375 | 11-oxo-beta-amyrin 30-oxidase activity | 1.14.14.115 |\\n| GO:0102556 | dammarenediol 12-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.120 |\\n| GO:0102557 | protopanaxadiol 6-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.121 |\\n| GO:0102596 | cytochrome P450 dependent ent-sandaracopimaradiene 3-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.70 |\\n| GO:0102597 | 3alpha-hydroxy-ent-sandaracopimardiene 9-beta-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.122 |\\n| GO:0102598 | 3alpha-hydroxy-ent-sandaracopimardiene 7-beta-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.123 |\\n| GO:0102684 | L-phenylalanine N-monooxygenase activity | 1.14.14.40 |\\n| GO:0102811 | geraniol 10-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.83 |\\n| GO:0102876 | psoralen synthase (NADPH) activity | 1.14.14.141 |\\n| GO:0102934 | costunolide synthase activity | 1.14.14.150 |\\n| GO:0102995 | angelicin synthase activity | 1.14.14.148 |\\n| GO:0106144 | fraxetin 5-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.164 |\\n| GO:0106149 | indole-3-carbonyl nitrile 4-hydroxylase activity | 1.14.14.165 |\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nIdentified as the largest cluster of EC/GO hierarchy inconsistencies in a programmatic review of the GO:0016491 oxidoreductase subtree: each term's `skos:exactMatch` EC is in sub-subclass 1.14.14, but the nearest EC-bearing is_a ancestor (GO:0016709) carries EC:1.14.13.-, which is not an EC-class ancestor of 1.14.14.x.\\n\\n## Suggested fix\\n\\nFor each term above, replace `is_a: GO:0016709` with `is_a: GO:0016712` (or a more specific descendant of GO:0016712 where one exists).\",\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"Reparent 49 EC:1.14.14.x terms from GO:0016709 to GO:0016712 (CYP450 reclassification)\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31967\"\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
